      },
      "date": "2014-07-08 19:36:54.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nYes, there were a number of changes to the GFP flags as we added and removed the CFS_ compatibility shims.  Lustre code always expects the memory to be zeroed, but I think this is moving in the right direction to have it handled by specifying the __GFP_ZERO flag, and then we could theoretically move this out to the callers and drop the flag in the cases where we don't need it.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
